# Import Conventions

Within a package, use relative imports. Between packages, use absolute imports from the project root (`backend/`).

## Within-package (relative)

```python
# In models/orm.py (same package as models/database.py)
from .database import Base
from .enums import ForecastStatus

# In api/main.py (same package as api/routers/)
from .routers import forecast_areas, forecasts
```

## Cross-package (absolute from project root)

```python
# In api/deps.py (importing from models and config packages)
from models.database import build_engine
from config import settings
```

## Never

```python
# Don't use absolute imports for within-package references
from models.database import Base  # Wrong if you're inside models/orm.py
```
